{"title_page": "List of Royal College Colombo alumni", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{multiple issues|{{overly detailed|list=yes|date=August 2015}}\n{{very long|list|date=August 2015}}\n{{Alumni|date=December 2014}}}}\n{{Dynamic list}}\n[[File:Royal_College,_Colombo-Logo.png|right]]\n\nThis is a list of alumni of [[Royal College Colombo]] in [[Sri Lanka]], often called '''\"Old Royalists\"'''.\n<!---only persons with wiki pages should be added, entries must have class year and citation to tie them to school per [[WP:NLIST]] & [[WP:PEOPLE]]--->\n\n{{Quote box\n |quote  = One comes across fellow Royalists in varying situations in life; <br />instantly a rapport is established for one knows the other<br /> \u2014 assumes his qualities and understands his character.\n |author = [[Lalith Athulathmudali]]\n |source =\n |quoted = \n}}\n\n==Heads of State==\n[[File:Junius Richard Jayawardana (1906-1996).jpg|thumb|J. R. Jayewardene, President of Sri Lanka|140px]] \n[[File:Maumoon-Abdul-Gayoom.jpg |thumb|Maumoon Abdul Gayoom, President of the Maldives|140px]]\n[[File:Sir James Peiris.JPG |thumb|Sir James Peiris, Vice President of the Legislative Council and first Ceylonese Acting Governor|140px]]\n[[File:Anagarika Dharmapala.jpg |thumb|Anagarika Dharmapala,<br /> Buddhist revivalist and writer|140px]]\n\n{{AlumniStart}}\n\n{{Alum\n|name=[[J. R. Jayewardene]]\n|year= \n|nota= [[President of Sri Lanka|President]] (1978&ndash;1989), [[Prime Minister of Sri Lanka]] (1978&ndash;1979), member of [[Sri Lanka Parliament|Parliament]] [[Kelaniya Electoral District|Kelaniya]] (1960), [[Colombo South Electoral District|Colombo South]] (1960&ndash;1977), [[Colombo West Electoral District|Colombo West]] (1977&ndash;1978)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Maumoon Abdul Gayoom]]\n|year= \n|nota=[[President of the Maldives]] (1978&ndash;2008)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Muhammad Fareed Didi]]\n|year= \n|nota= [[List of Sultans of the Maldives|Sultan of the Maldives]] (1954&ndash;1968)\n|ref=<ref name=\"Royalty\">{{cite web|url=http://www.maldivesroyalfamily.com/maldives_photo_10.shtml |title=Maldive students at Royal College Colombo 1920s |publisher=Maldivesroyalfamily.com |date=16 January 2008|accessdate=10 September 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{AlumniEnd}}\n\n==Heads of Government==\n\n{{AlumniStart}}\n\n{{Alum\n|name=[[John Lionel Kotalawela|Sir John Kotalawela]] \n|year= \n|nota= [[Prime Minister of Ceylon]] (1953&ndash;1956), [[Parliament of Ceylon|member of Parliament]] for [[Dodangaslanda Electoral District|Dodangaslanda]] (1947&ndash;1959), [[Legislative Council of Ceylon|member of Legislative Council]] (?&ndash;1931), [[State Council of Ceylon|member of State Council]] (1931&ndash;1947)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Ranil Wickremesinghe]]\n|year= \n|nota=[[Prime Minister of Sri Lanka|Prime Minister]] (1993&ndash;1994, 2001&ndash;2004, 2015&ndash;present)\n|ref=\n}}\n\n{{AlumniEnd}}\n\n==Royalty==\n{{AlumniStart}}\n\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Prince]] [[Henveyru Ganduvaru Manippulu]]\n|year= \n|nota= [[Crown Prince]] of the [[Maldives]]\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Prince]] [[Hassan Farid Didi]] \n|year= \n|nota=Minister for Home Affairs, Minister for Finance, Minister of State and Plenipotentiary Representative in Ceylon\n|ref=\n}}\n{{AlumniEnd}}\n\n==Viceregal==\n{{AlumniStart}}\n\n{{Alum\n|name=[[James Peiris|Sir James Peiris]]\n|year= \n|nota= Acting [[Governors of British Ceylon|Governor of Ceylon]] (1925), Vice-President [[Legislative Council of Ceylon]] (1924&ndash;1940)\n|ref=<ref name=Presided/><ref name=Acting>[http://www.atimes.com/ind-pak/CI08Df01.html Chapter 5: SRI LANKA: THE UNTOLD STORY], K.T.Rajasingham [[Asia Times]] Retrieved 7 November 2015</ref>\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[C. Nagalingam]]\n|year=\n|nota=Acting [[Governor-General of Ceylon]] (1954), Acting [[Chief Justice of Sri Lanka|Chief Justice of Ceylon]] (1954), [[List of Justices of the Supreme Court of Sri Lanka|Supreme Court Judge]] (1947&ndash;1958), [[Attorney General of Sri Lanka|Attorney General]] (1946&ndash;1947)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[David de Kretser]]\n|year=\n|nota=[[Governors of Victoria|Governor of Victoria]] (2006&ndash;2011)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{AlumniEnd}}\n\n==Prominent figures in the Independence Movement==\n{{AlumniStart}}\n\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Anagarika Dharmapala]]\n|year=\n|nota=Buddhist revivalist and leader of the Sri Lankan independence movement \n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[James Peiris|Sir James Peiris]]\n|year=\n|nota=Prominent political leader, first Vice President of the Legislative Council and the first Ceylonese Acting Governor\n|ref=<ref name=Presided>[https://books.google.com/books?id=jUTf-jaS2xAC&printsec=frontcover&dq=isbn:1463418388&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCEQ6wEwAGoVChMIsfTTtNuAyQIVRqQOCh1eVQi_#v=onepage&q=Peiris%20presided%20over%20Legislative%20Council%20Administering%20Government&f=false PEACE AT LAST IN PARADISE], Ananda Guruge p.213 (AuthorHouse Publishing) {{ISBN|9781463418373}}</ref> (note: also listed in Legislators)\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Fredrick Richard Senanayake|F. R. Senanayake]]\n|year=\n|nota=Leader of the Sri Lankan independence movement and member of [[Legislative Council of Ceylon]] (note: also listed in Legislators)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[E. W. Perera]]\n|year=\n|nota=[[Senate of Ceylon|Senator]], member of Legislative Council and [[State Council of Ceylon|State Council]] \n|ref= (note: also listed in Legislators)\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Ponnambalam Ramanathan|Sir Ponnambalam Ramanathan]]\n|year=\n|nota=Prominent political leader, [[Solicitor General of Ceylon]] and first member to be elected to the Legislative Council\n|ref=<ref name=\"indi\">{{cite web |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2008/02/10/jun06.asp |title=Those who led the independence struggle |publisher=Sundayobserver.lk |accessdate=2011-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605192811/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2008/02/10/jun06.asp |archive-date=2011-06-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> (note: also listed in Legislators and Civil servants)\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Ponnambalam Arunachalam|Sir Ponnambalam Arunachalam]]\n|year=\n|nota=Prominent political leader of Ceylon, member of the [[Executive Council (Commonwealth countries)|Executive Council]] and Legislative Council\n|ref=<ref name=\"indi\"/> (note: also listed in Legislators)\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Charles Edgar Corea]]\n|year=\n|noa=Prominent leader in the independence movement, Member of the Legislative Council and President of the Ceylon National Congress\n|ref=(also listed in Legislators)\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Henry Pedris]]\n|year=\n|nota=[[Colombo Town Guard|CTG]] \u2013 prominent figure executed by the British\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Charles Alwis Hewavitharana]]\n|year=\n|nota=Prominent leader in the independence movement \n|ref=(note: also listed in Medicine)\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Armand de Souza]]\n|year=\n|nota=leading editorialist who campaigned for democratisation of the legislature\n|ref=\n}}\n\n{{AlumniEnd}}\n\n==Politics==\n===Heads of Legislature===\n{{AlumniStart}}\n\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Forester Augustus Obeysekera|Sir Forester Obeysekera]]\n|year=\n|nota=[[Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|Speaker]] of the [[State Council of Ceylon]] (1934&ndash;1935), member [[Legislative Council of Ceylon|Legislative Council]] (1924&ndash;1931)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Gerard Wijeyekoon|Sir Gerard Wijeyekoon]]\n|year=\n|nota=First [[President of the Senate of Ceylon]] (1947&ndash;1953)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Nicholas Attygalle|Sir Nicholas Attygalle]]\n|year=\n|nota=First president [[Senate of Ceylon]] (1953&ndash;1960), first Ceylonese [[Chancellor (education)#Vice-chancellor|Vice-Chancellor]] [[University of Ceylon]] (1954&ndash;1967), President Ceylon Medical Council\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Cyril de Zoysa|Sir Cyril de Zoysa]] \n|year=\n|nota=[[President of the Senate of Ceylon]] (1960&ndash;1965)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Abeyratne Ratnayaka]]\n|year= \n|nota=[[President of the Senate of Ceylon]] (1965&ndash;1971), [[Parliament of Ceylon|member of Parliament]] for [[Wattegama Electoral District|Wattegama]] (1947&ndash;1956, 1960&ndash;1965)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Shirley Corea]]\n|year=\n|nota=[[Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|Speaker of Parliament]] (1967&ndash;1970), [[Parliament of Ceylon|member of Parliament]] for [[Chilaw Electoral District|Chilaw]] (1952&ndash;1970)\n|ref=\n}}\n{{Alum\n|name=[[Anura Bandaranaike]]\n|year=\n|nota=[[Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|Speaker of Parliament]] (2000&ndash;2001), [[Parliament of Ceylon|member of Parliament]] for [[Nuwara Eliya-Maskeliya Electoral District|Nuwara Eliya-Maskeliya]] (1977&ndash;1989)\n|ref=\n}}\n\n{{AlumniEnd}}\n\n===Ministers and legislators===\n==== Current ====\n;National Government benches\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:*;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:65%;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notability\n! style=\"width:*;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Reference(s)\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ranil|Wickremesinghe}}\n| [[Parliament of Sri Lanka|Member of Parliament]] \u2013 [[Prime Minister of Sri Lanka|Prime Minister]] (note: also listed in Heads of State and Heads of Government)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Mangala|Samaraweera}}\n| [[Parliament of Sri Lanka|Member of Parliament]] \u2013 [[Minister of Foreign Affairs of Sri Lanka|Cabinet Minister of Foreign Affairs]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ravi|Karunanayake}}\n| [[Parliament of Sri Lanka|Member of Parliament]] \u2013 [[Minister of Finance (Sri Lanka)|Cabinet Minister of Finance]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Lakshman|Kiriella}}\n| [[Parliament of Sri Lanka|Member of Parliament]] \u2013 [[Ministry of Highways, Ports & Shipping|Cabinet Minister of Highways]], [[Leader of the House (Sri Lanka)|Leader of the House]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Sajith|Premadasa}}\n| [[Parliament of Sri Lanka|Member of Parliament]] \u2013