~lkawgw/gen197.html Maas Thajoon Akbar, KC 1880-1944]</ref> (note: also listed in Judges and lawyers)\n* [[Charles Edgar Corea|C.E. Corea]] \u2013 former Member of the Legislative Council, President of the Ceylon National Congress (1924)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesundayleader.lk/20090628/REVIEW.HTM |title=A national hero is honoured in his home town |publisher=Thesundayleader.lk |date= |accessdate=2011-09-10}}</ref> (note: also listed in Prominent figures in the Independence Movement)\n* [[Charles Ambrose Lorensz]] \u2013 former Member of the Legislative Council (note: also listed in Judges)\n* [[T M Sabaratnam]] \u2013 former Member of the Legislative Council\n* [[James De Alwis]] \u2013 former Member of the Legislative Council<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">[http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2011/05/08/mon01.asp Not promoting the pretensions of' \u2018literary theory'] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514065642/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2011/05/08/mon01.asp |date=2011-05-14 }}</ref> (note: also listed in Poets)\n* [[K. Balasingam]] \u2013 former Member of the Executive Council and Legislative Council\n* [[J. R. Weinman]] \u2013 former Member of the Legislative Council (note: also listed in Judges)\n* [[Saifee Villa#History and Alfred Joseph Richard de Soysa|A. J. R. de Soysa]] \u2013 former Member of the Legislative Council of Ceylon\n\n==Judiciary==\n;Chief Justices\n* [[Miliani Sansoni]] \u2013 former [[Chief Justice of Ceylon|Chief Justice]] of the [[Supreme Court of Ceylon]]\n* [[Hugh Norman Gregory Fernando]] \u2013 former Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Ceylon<ref name=\"A Historic Injustice\"/>\n* [[Parinda Ranasinghe]] \u2013 former Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Sri Lanka<ref>{{cite web|author=Information Laboratories (Pvt.) Ltd. |url=http://sundaytimes.lk/990321/mudli.html |title=The rise of Sinhala in our courts \u2013 Part II |publisher=Sundaytimes.lk |date=1999-03-21 |accessdate=2011-09-10}}</ref>\n* [[Mohan Peiris]] <small