 brush and palette]</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Rukshan|Perera}}\n| Musician\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>[http://sundaytimes.lk/110102/Magazine/sundaytimesmagazine_04.html A feast for fans from Rukshan]</ref>\n|}\n\n==Activists==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:*;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:65%;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notability\n! style=\"width:*;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Reference(s)\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ajith C. S.|Perera}}\n| [[List of disability rights activists|Disability rights activist]], [[Chief executive officer|Chief Executive]] / [[chief operating officer|Secretary-General]]\u2013 [[Idiriya]] (2016&ndash;present)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite news | last = Perera | first = Ajith C. S. | title = Cricket where Everybody is Included | work = Features Page 8 | publisher = Upali Newspapers - The Island | date = 19 August 2008 | url = http://www.island.lk/2008/08/19/features3.html | accessdate = 30 January 2009 | quote= Although now a wheelchair user, Perera remains very much 'Not Out' as a pioneer disability activist, promoting ''Environments that are Accessible and dis-Abled Friendly'' especially at Sports venues.}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Bala|Tampoe}}\n| [[General Secretary]] of the [[Ceylon Mercantile Union|Ceylon Mercantile, Industrial and General Workers Union]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Percy|Wickremasekera}}\n| [[General Secretary]] of the [[United Corporations and Mercantile Union]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Kumar|Ponnambalam}}\n| Leader of [[All Ceylon Tamil Congress]], [[1982 Sri Lankan presidential election|Presidential candidate (1982)]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|}\n\n==Religion==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:*;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:65%;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notability\n! style=\"width:*;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Reference(s)\n|-\n| {{sortname|Lakdasa|De Mel}}\n| First