ilake}}\n| Neurologist, Head of Department of Medicine, [[University of Kelaniya]], Professor of Medicine [[University of Sri Jayawardanapura]], President Ceylon College of Physicians\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"Saman\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Sanath|Lamabathusooriya}}\n| Paediatrician, Dean [[Faculty of Medicine, University of Colombo]] (2002&ndash;2005)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<!-- Reference: http://www.silumina.lk/2010/06/06/_art.asp?fn=ay1006061 -->\n|-\n| {{sortname|Janaka|de Silva}}\n| Physician, President of Ceylon College of Physicians, Chairman [[National Research Council of Sri Lanka]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Susirith|Mendis}}\n| Physician, [[Chancellor (education)#Vice-Chancellor|Vice-Chancellor]] [[University of Ruhuna]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Nalin|Rodrigo}}\n| Obstetrician, gynaecologist, surgeon, Medical Director Asha Central Hospital, Chairman Sri Jayawardanapura General Hospital\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|U. S.|Jayawickrama}}\n| Endocrinologist, founder Diabetes Association of Sri Lanka \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Surendra|Ramachandran}}\n| [[Nephrology|Nephrologist]], founder of Sri Lanka's first Dialysis Unit, President of Ceylon College of Physicians\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|H. H. R.|Samarasinghe}}\n| Physician, medical administrator, president of Sri Lanka Medical Council\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Charles Alwis|Hewavitharana}}\n| Physician, member University College Ceylon Council\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Maiya|Gunasekera}}\n| Surgeon, President [[Sri Lankan Rugby Football Union]] (1998&ndash;1999) \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Rezvi|Sheriff}}\n| Emeritus Professor of Medicine, [[University of Colombo]], Physician first trained Nephrologist, President Sri Lanka Medical Council, Ceylon College of Physician, Founder Na