34294.html|title=Mike Will \u2013 Est. in 1989 Pt. 2.5 // Free Mixtape|work=[[DatPiff]]|publisher=Idle Media Inc|date=2012-12-24|accessdate=2014-01-04}}</ref>\n* Label: Self-released\n* Formats: Digital download\n* Hosted by [[DJ Drama]]\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''#MikeWiLLBeenTriLL''\n|\n* Released: December 23, 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.datpiff.com/Mike-Will-MikeWillBeenTrill-mixtape.563373.html|title=Mike Will \u2013 #MikeWillBeenTrill // Free Mixtape|work=[[DatPiff]]|publisher=Idle Media Inc|date=2013-06-25|accessdate=2014-01-04}}</ref>\n* Label: Self-released\n* Formats: Digital download\n* Hosted by [[Future (rapper)|Future]]\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Ransom''\n|\n* Released: December 15, 2014<ref>{{cite tweet|user=MikeWiLLMadeIt|author=Mike WiLL Made It \ud83e\udd8d|number=537283261119365120|date=25 November 2014|title=#RANSOM (( ALL NEW MUSIC. ))                 DECEMBER 15 \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25}}</ref>\n* Label: Ear Drummer Records\n* Formats: Digital download\n| \u2014 || 45 || 4 \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Gotti Made-It]]'' <br />{{small|(with [[Yo Gotti]])}}\n|\n* Released: June 1, 2017<ref name=\"GMI\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2017/06/yo-gotti-nicki-minaj-rake-it-up|title=Yo Gotti and Mike Will Made-It Drop Collab Project 'Gotti Made-It' f/ Nicki Minaj|date=June 1, 2017|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|access-date=June 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* Label: Self-released\n* Formats: [[Streaming media|Streaming]], digital download\n| 40 || 7 || \u2014\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{{BLP sources section|date=June 2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions and certifications, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:21em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard Hot 100|US]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B/HH]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Hot Rap Songs|US Rap]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[GfK Entertainment Charts|GER]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"[[23 (song)|23]]\"<br/><small>(featuring [[Miley Cyrus]], [[Wiz Khalifa]] and [[Juicy J]])</small>\n| 2013\n| 11 || 2 || 2 || 39 || 78 || 26 || 30 || 85\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Buy the World\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases |title=Top 40 Rhythmic Future Releases |publisher=All Access Music Group |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6QnuDj2If?url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases |archivedate=2014-07-04 |url-status=dead }}</ref><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[Future (rapper)|Future]], [[Lil Wayne]] and [[Kendrick Lamar]])\n| 2014\n| \u2014 || 42 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 \n|rowspan=\"3\"| ''Ransom''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Drinks On Us\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/drinks-on-us-feat.-weeknd/id974219390|title=Drinks On Us (feat. The Weeknd, Swae Lee & Future) - Single|publisher=iTunes}}</ref><br/><small>(featuring [[Swae Lee]], [[The Weeknd]] and Future)</small>\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| \u2014 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Drinks On Us\" did not enter the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs chart, but peaked at number five on the Bubbling Under R&B/Hip-Hop Singles chart.<ref name=\"BubblingR&B\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5b0%5d=ts_chart_artistname%3AMike+Will+Made+It&f%5b1%5d=itm_field_chart_id%3A345&f%5b2%5d=ss_bb_type%3Achart_item&type=2&artist=Mike+Will+Made+It|title=Chart Search for Mike Will Made It (Bubbling Under R&B/Hip-Hop Singles) &#124; Billboard|work=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2017}}</ref>}} || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Choppin' Blades\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/choppin-blades-feat.-jody/id975909673|title=Choppin' Blades (feat. Jody HiGHROLLER & Slim Jxmmi) - Single by Mike Will Made-It|publisher=iTunes}}</ref><br/><small>(featuring [[Jody Highroller]] and [[Slim Jxmmi]])</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"[[Nothing Is Promised]]\"<br/><small>(with [[Rihanna]])</small>\n| 2016\n| 75 || 26 || \u2014 || 69 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 25 || 64\n| ''Ransom 2''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[It Takes Two (Rob Base & DJ E-Z Rock song)#Mike Will Made It, Carly Rae Jepsen and Lil Yachty version|It Takes Two]]\"<br/><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(with [[Carly Rae Jepsen]] and [[Lil Yachty]])</span>\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2017\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Gucci On My\"<br/><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[21 Savage]], [[YG (rapper)|YG]], and [[Migos]])</span>\n| \u2014{{efn-ua|\"Gucci On My\" did not enter the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, but peaked at number 10 on the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles]] chart.<ref name=\"Bubbling\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D=ts_chart_artistname%3AMike+Will+Made+It&f%5B1%5D=itm_field_chart_id%3A344&f%5B2%5D=ss_bb_type%3Achart_item&type=2&artist=Mike+Will+Made+It|title=Mike Will Mad