-album-single/1440544929|title=Kill 'Em With Success (From \"Creed II: The Album\") - Single by Eearz, ScHoolboy Q, 2 Chainz & Mike WiLL Made-It|publisher=[[iTunes Store]]|access-date=November 5, 2018}}</ref><br/><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(with Eearz, [[Schoolboy Q|ScHoolboy Q]] and [[2 Chainz]])</span>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Creed II: The Album]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Mantra\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-mantra-from-creed-ii-the-album-single/1441800096|title=The Mantra (From \"Creed II: The Album\") - Single by Mike WiLL Made-It, Pharrell Williams & Kendrick Lamar on Apple Music|publisher=[[iTunes Store]]|access-date=November 16, 2018}}</ref><br />{{small|(with [[Pharrell Williams|Pharrell]] and Kendrick Lamar)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"The Mantra\" did not enter the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs chart, but peaked at number 47 on the [[R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay]] chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/mike-will-made-it/chart-history/hot-r-and-b-hip-hop-airplay|title=Mike Will Made-It Chart History (R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=December 5, 2018}}</ref>}} || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n|colspan=\"14\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n==== Promotional singles ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions and certifications, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:21em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard Hot 100|US]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B/HH]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Hot Rap Songs|US Rap]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[GfK Entertainment Charts|GER]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Black Barbies (song)|Black Barbies]]\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(with [[Nicki Minaj]])\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2017\n| 65 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 47 || - || 78 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"1\"{{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"14\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n=== BET Hip Hop Awards ===\nThe [[BET Hip Hop Awards]] were established in 2006 by the [[Black Entertainment Television]] network to celebrate [[hip hop music|hip-hop]] performers, producers and [[music video]] directors.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Nomination\n!Award\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[2013 Bet Hip Hop Awards|2013]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|\"[[Bugatti (song)|Bugatti]]\"\n|Track of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibe.com/2013/08/kendrick-lamar-leads-list-nominees-2013-bet-hip-hop-awards/|title=Kendrick Lamar Leads List Of Nominees For 2013 BET Hip Hop Awards|Vibe=|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1715658/bet-hip-hop-awards-2013-winners/|title=2013 BET Hip Hop Awards: The Complete Winners List|work=mtv.com|accessdate=13 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Club Banger\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Mike Will Made It\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Producer of the Year\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=