{"title_page": "Park Hyung-sik", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean actor and singer}}\n{{Korean name|Park}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{EngvarB|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Park Hyung-sik\n| image              = Park_Hyung-sik_at_the_Chanel_Paris_event_in_Seoul,_28th_May_2019.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = Hyungsik in May 2019\n| native_name        = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1991|11|16}}\n| birth_place        = [[Yongin]], South Korea\n| education          = \n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|actor}}\n| spouse             = \n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed           = yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[dance music|Dance]]}}\n| years_active    = {{Start date|2010}}\u2013present\n| label           = {{hlist|[[Star Empire Entertainment|Star Empire]]|United Artists Agency}}\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[ZE:A]]|ZE:A Five}}\n| website         = {{URL|https://web.archive.org/web/20130512010407/http://ze-a.com|ZE:A}}\n| alias           = \n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n| child  = yes\n| color  = transparent\n| hangul = {{linktext|\ubc15|\ud615|\uc2dd}}\n| hanja  = {{linktext|\u6734|\u70af|\u690d}}\n| rr     = Bak Hyeong-sik\n| mr     = Pak Hy\u014fngsik\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Park Hyung-sik''' (born November 16, 1991),<ref name=\"Russell2014\">{{cite book|author=Mark Russell|title=K-Pop Now!: The Korean Music Revolution|page=68|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=etDZAwAAQBAJ|date=April 29, 2014|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|isbn=978-1-4629-1411-1}}</ref> known mononymously as '''Hyungsik''', is a South Korean singer, actor and dancer. He is a member of the South Korean boy group, [[ZE:A]] and its sub-group ZE:A Five. As an actor, he is known for his roles in ''[[The Heirs]]'' (2013), ''[[High Society (2015 TV series)|High Society]]'' (2015), ''[[Hwarang: The Poet Warrior Youth]]'' (2016),  ''[[Strong Girl Bong-soon]]'' (2017), and [[Suits (South Korean TV series)|''Suits'']] (2018). He stars in drama series, as well as in movies and music theatre productions.\n\n== Personal life ==\nPark was born in [[Yongin]], [[Gyeonggi Province]], South Korea as the second of two sons.{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}} He was named Hyung-sik (\ud615\uc2dd, \u70af\u690d) by a Buddhist monk, as his mother and grandmother are Buddhists.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/117910|title=\ubc15\ud615\uc2dd\u2502My name is\u2026|last=\ud3b8\uc9d1\uad6d|date=January 23, 2013|work=10Asia|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\n=== Military Enlistment ===\nPark began his [[Conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]] on June 10, 2019. He entered the Nonsan Army Recruit Training Center in [[South Chungcheong Province]] to start his basic military training and will be completing the rest of his military duties in the military police department of the Capital Defense Command as an active duty soldier.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/07/398_270379.html|title=Park Hyung-sik starts mandatory military service|date=2019-06-10|website=koreatimes|language=en|access-date=2019-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/ap/news/1048407/park-hyung-sik-has-officially-enlisted-for-military-service|title=Park Hyung-Sik Has Officially Enlisted For Military Service|date=June 10, 2019|website=E! Online|language=en|access-date=2019-07-26}}</ref>\n\nPark had earlier revealed that he was inspired to join the Capital Defense Command after he received positive feedback for his shooting skills while training for the variety show, [[Real Man (TV series)|Real Man]]. The actor said that he wanted to put his skills to good use, so he is excited to join the unit and be of service to his country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.businesstimes.cn/articles/113501/20190611/park-hyung-sik-begins-training-for-2-year-mandatory-service-as-active-duty-soldier.htm|title=Park Hyung Sik Begins Training For 2-year Mandatory Service As Active Duty Soldier|last=Times|first=Business|date=2019-06-11|website=Business Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-26}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n=== 2009: Pre-debut ===\nIn February 2009, Park appeared in [[Jewelry (band)|Jewelry S]]' \"Date\" music video as the male lead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2013/08/25/2013082500404.html|title=\ubc15\ud615\uc2dd 4\ub144 \uc804, \uc8fc\uc5bc\ub9acS \ubba4\uc9c1\ube44\ub514\uc624\uc5d0 \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026 '\uc544\uae30\ubcd1\uc0ac'\uc758 \uc7a5\ubc1c \u2018\ub208\uae38\u2019|date=August 25, 2013|website=The Chosun Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref> The same year, Park worked as a uniform brand model<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.asiatoday.co.kr/view.php?key=318128|title=\uc81c\uad6d\uc758 \uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uba64\ubc84\ubcc4 \ud504\ub85c\ud544 \uacf5\uac1c '\ucf00\ube48\u00b7\uc784\uc2dc\uc644\u00b7\ubc15\ud615\uc2dd'|work=Asia Today|date=January 13, 2010|access-date=April 16, 2017|language=ko}}</ref> and also appeared in [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s reality program ''ZE:A's Debut Diary'' along with fellow ZE:A members.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=009&aid=0002089654|title=\uc5f0\uc608\uacc4 \ub4b7\uc598\uae30 `\uc81c\uad6d\uc758 \uc544\uc774\ub4e4`\u2026100% `\ub9ac\uc5bc` \uac00\ub2a5\ud560\uae4c?|date=April 6, 2009|access-date=April 16, 2017|language=ko|website=MK}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002000932|title=\uc81c\uad6d\uc758 \uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uac70\ub9ac\uacf5\uc5f0\uc73c\ub85c \ud638\ub41c \ub370\ubdd4 \uc900\ube44\uc911|date=October 1, 2009|access-date=April 16, 2017|language=ko|website=Money Today}}</ref>\n\n=== 2010\u20132014: ZE:A, acting debut, and ZE:A Five ===\n{{Main|ZE:A}}\nOn January 7, 2010, Park debuted as a member of South Korean [[boy band]] [[ZE:A]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20100117n02678|title=\uc81c\uad6d\uc758 \uc544\uc774\ub4e4, '\ub9c8\uc824\ud1a0\ube0c' \ubb34\ub300 \uc131\uacf5\uc801 \ub370\ubdd4|website=\ub124\uc774\ud2b8\ub274\uc2a4|language=ko-KR|date=January 17, 2010|access-date=April 16, 2017}}</ref> In addition to ZE:A's regular promotional activities, he participated in variety shows and had [[bit part]]s in several dramas. In 2011, Park began his theatrical career as a cast member alongside [[Super Junior]]'s [[Ryeowook]] in the musical ''[[Temptation of Wolves]]''.<ref name=wolves>{{Cite news|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=103&oid=213&aid=0000106804|title=\uc81c\uad6d\uc758\uc544\uc774\ub4e4 \ubc15\ud615\uc2dd \ubba4\uc9c0\uceec '\ub291\ub300\uc758\uc720\ud639' \uce90\uc2a4\ud305|access-date=April 16, 2017|date=June 1, 2011|language=ko|website=TV Report}}</ref>\n\nHe began his acting career in 2012, starring in [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]' special drama ''I Remember You''.<ref name=remember>{{Cite news|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=213&aid=0000171932|title=\uae40\ubcd1\ub9cc \uc774\uc601\uc740 \uae40\uc9c4\uc6b0, \uc124\ud2b9\uc9d1 \ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ub110 \uae30\uc5b5\ud574'\ub85c '\uc548\ubc29\uadf9\uc7a5 \ud6c8\ud6c8'|access-date=April 16, 2017|language=ko|date=January 13, 2012|website=TV Report}}</ref> The same year, he starred in SBS' ''[[Dummy Mommy]]'', where he played a vocalist of an indie band.<ref name=dummy>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002279912|title='\ubc14\ubcf4\uc5c4\ub9c8' \ubc15\ud615\uc2dd \"\uc784\uc2dc\uc644, \ub108\ubb34 \ubc14\ube60 \uc5f0\uae30\uc870\uc5b8 \uad6c\ud560 \uc2dc\uac04 \uc5c6\ub2e4\"|access-date=April 16, 2017|date=March 13, 2012|language=ko|website=Herald Corporation}}</ref>\n\nThe following year, Park had a role in [[KBS2]]'s drama special ''Sirius'' (2013), where he played the adolescent version of two twin brothers with starkly contrasting personalities.<ref name=\"sirius\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.fnnews.com/news/201301041112312139|title='\uc2dc\ub9ac\uc6b0\uc2a4' \ubc15\ud615\uc2dd, \ucd9c\uc5f0\uc18c\uac10 \"\uc784\uc2dc\uc644 \uacbd\ud5d8-\ud669\uad11\ud76c \uc751\uc6d0 \ub3c4\uc6c0\ub3fc\"|website=FN News|language=ko|date=January 4, 2013|access-date=April 16, 2017}}</ref> It was also in early 2013 when Park participated in his second musical theatre production, ''[[Gwanghwamun Love Song]]'', playing the role of Ji-Yong.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.obs.co.kr/news_view.php?id=668224|title=[ONEWS] \uc81c\uad6d\uc758\uc544\uc774\ub4e4 \ud615\uc2dd-\ucf00\ube48 '\ubba4\uc9c0\uceec '\uad11\ud654\ubb38 \uc5f0\uac00'\ub85c \ub9cc\ub098\uc694'|last=OBS|website=OBS NEWS|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2013, Park, along with his fellow ZE:A members Siwan, Kevin, Minwoo and Dongjun formed the group's first sub-unit called ''ZE:A Five''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/en/web/20170416130228/http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/31360/zea-unit-group-zea-five-to-debut-in-korea|title=ZE:A to Debut Five-Member Unit, ZE:A Five, in Korea|website=Mwave|language=en|date=March 14, 2013|access-date=April 16, 2017}}</ref> He then featured in tvN's time-slip drama ''[[Nine (TV series)|Nine]]'' as the younger version of [[Lee Jin-wook]]'s character.<ref name=\"nine\">{{cite web|url=https://sg.style.yahoo.com/news/ze-a-s-park-hyung-sik-finishes-shooting-091922973.html|title=ZE:A\u2032s Park Hyung Sik Finishes Shooting for \u2032Nine\u2032 Amidst Praise from Staff|website=Mwave|date=May 7, 2013}}</ref>\n\nPark gained wider recognition after joining ''[[Real Men (TV series)|Real Men]]'' in June 2013, where he was nicknamed \"Baby Soldier\" for his innocent, yet passionate image.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2991986|title=Park Hyung-sik to depart \u2018Real Men\u2019|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|date=July 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, Park was cast as Clyde in his third musical theatre production, [[Bonnie & Clyde (musical)|''Bonnie & Clyde'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/65517|title=SHINee Key, ZE:A Hyungsik Cast in Musical \"Bonnie & Clyde\"|last=Lee|first=Cory|date=2013-07-18|website=TENASIA|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> He followed this with a role in hit teen drama ''[[The Heirs]]'' (2013).\n\nIn early 2014, Park was cast for the role of [[Charles de Batz-Castelmore d'Artagnan|D'Artagnan]] in his fourth musical production, [[The Three Musketeers (musical)|''The Three Musketeers'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/01/688_151583.html|title='Three Musketeers' goes to Tokyo, Seoul|date=2014-02-13|website=koreatimes|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> And in August of the same year, Park joined the main cast of the family drama ''[[What's With This Family]]'' (2014) as Cha Dal-bong, the youngest child who is struggling with finding a stable job.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/en/web/20170729181215/http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/47614/hyung-siks-character-is-just-like-him|title=ZE:A\u2019s Hyung Sik says His Character Was Written for Him|website=Mwave|date=October 17, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"family\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mnetamerica.com/news/article/69723/park-hyung-sik-cast-for-this-is-family|title=ZE:A\u2032s Park Hyung Sik Cast in Drama \u2032This Is Family\u2032|website=Mwave|date=July 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015\u2013present: Solo career and new agency ===\nIn 2015, Park was part of the main cast in SBS' romance drama [[High Society (2015 TV series)|''High Society'']] where he played the role of a [[chaebol]] who falls for a part-timer at the gourmet supermarket he manages.<ref name=high>{{Cite news|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3002965|title=ZE:A's Park to star in drama|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|date=April 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3008011|title=Singer Park talks growing TV career|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|date=August 18, 2015}}</ref> Park drew favorable reviews for his performance in the series, which led to increased popularity for the actor in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/08/20/2015082000590.html|title=Boy Band Star Park Hyung-sik Finally Gains Acting Chops|website=The Chosun Ilbo|date=August 20, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2015/10/398_188716.html|title=Park Hyung-sik greets Japanese fans|website=The Korea Times|date=October 15, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn the following year, Park was once again cast for the role of [[Charles de Batz-Castelmore d'Artagnan|D'Artagnan]] in the 2016 musical production of [[The Three Musketeers (musical)|''The Three Musketeers'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20160410000306|title=\u2018Three Musketeers\u2019 returns to local stage with younger cast|last=Herald|first=The Korea|date=2016-04-10|website=www.koreaherald.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> And in December 2016, he starred in the historical drama ''[[Hwarang: The Poet Warrior Youth]]'', playing the role of [[Jinheung of Silla|Sammaekjong]], a young and distrustful king.<ref name=hwarang>{{Cite news|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2016/03/201_194659.html|title=Park Seo-joon, Park Hyung-sik and Go Ara to star in 'Hwarang'|work=The Korea Times|date=January 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, Park starred in his first leading role in cable network [[JTBC]]'s ''[[Strong Girl Bong-soon]]'', playing the CEO of a game company, Ainsoft.<ref name=strong>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201704121809441495963_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Park Bo-young, Park Hyung-sik wrap up filming for \u2018Strong Woman Do Bong-soon\u2019|date=April 12, 2017|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref>  The romantic-comedy with [[Park Bo-young]] was a critical and commercial success, and became one of the [[Korean drama#List of highest-rated Korean dramas in cable television|highest rated Korean dramas in cable television history]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201704161733316724032_2|title='Strong Woman Do Bong-soon' ends with JTBC's top viewership|date=April 16, 2017|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201703220100190310013427&servicedate=20170321|title=[SC\uc90c\u4eba] \"\ubc15\ud615\uc2dd \uc7a1\uc544\ub77c\" `\ub3c4\ubd09\uc21c` \uc778\uae30\uc5d0 \uad11\uace0 \ub7ec\ube0c\ucf5c \uae09\ub4f1|work=Sports Chosun|date=March 21, 2017|language=ko}}</ref>  Park experienced a rise in popularity<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2017/04/398_228106.html|title=[INTERVIEW] Actor Park Hyung-sik shakes off 'idol' tag|website=The Korea Times|date=April 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/search1/2603000000.html?cid=AEN20170421005200315|title=(Yonhap Interview) 'Acting helped me tap inner self': Park Hyung-sik\n|website=Yonhap News Agnency|date=April 21, 2017}}</ref> and received increased endorsement offers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201703220100190310013427&servicedate=20170321|title=[SC\uc90c\u4eba] \"\ubc15\ud615\uc2dd \uc7a1\uc544\ub77c\" `\ub3c4\ubd09\uc21c` \uc778\uae30\uc5d0 \uad11\uace0 \ub7ec\ube0c\ucf5c \uae09\ub4f1|work=Sports Chosun|date=March 21, 2017|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Park officially signed with United Artists Agency (UAA) after deciding not to renew with his former agency, Star Empire Entertainment.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3032152|title=Park Hyung-sik signs with United Artists|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|date=April 12, 2017}}</ref> In December 2017, he starred in a romantic short film, ''Two Rays of Light'' alongside [[Han Ji-min]].<ref name=\"light\">{{cite web|url=http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/news/news.jsp?pageIndex=1&blbdComCd=601006&seq=4596&mode=VIEW&returnUrl=&searchKeyword=|title=HUR Jin-ho Returns with New Short Film|date=December 8, 2017|work=Korean Film Biz Zone}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, Park starred in the [[Suits (South Korean TV series)|Korean remake]] of American [[legal drama]] series ''[[Suits (U.S. TV series)|Suits]]''; portraying the Korean counterpart of Mike Ross.<ref name=\"suits\">{{Cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2017/09/25/2017092500716.html|title=Jang Dong-gun, Park Hyung-sik to Star in Remake of U.S. TV Series|date=September 25, 2017|website=The Chosun Ilbo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20180423000893|title=Lawyers to wear tailored \u2018Suits\u2019 in Korea|date=April 24, 2018|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref> Following this, in November 2018, Park returned to the musical scene, playing the role of Der Tod in the stage production of [[Elisabeth (musical)|''Elisabeth'']].\n\nIn 2019, Park made his feature film debut in the legal film ''[[Juror 8]]''.<ref name=juror>{{cite web|url=http://koreanfilm.or.kr/eng/news/news.jsp?pageIndex=1&blbdComCd=601006&seq=4904&mode=VIEW&returnUrl=&searchKeyword=|title=THE JURORS Is in Session with MOON So-ri and PARK Hyung-sik|date=July 23, 2018|website=Korean Film Biz Zone}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/05/04/2019050400278.html|title=Park Hyung-sik Speaks out on Big Screen Debut|date=May 4, 2019|website=The Chosun Ilbo}}</ref> This role won him the Best New Actor award at the 39th [[Korean Association of Film Critics Awards]] in November 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=416&aid=0000250245|title='\uae30\uc0dd\ucda9', \uc81c39\ud68c \uc601\ud3c9\uc0c1 3\uad00\uc655\u2026\uc2e0\ud558\uade0\u00b7\uae40\ud5a5\uae30 \ub0a8\ub140\uc8fc\uc5f0\uc0c1|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|ZE:A discography}}\n\n===As artist===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! Peak chart <br> positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Sales<br><small>([[Music download|DL]])</small>\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! style=\"width=3em;font-size:90%\"|[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR<br>Gaon]]<br><ref>Charted songs:\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=16&hitYear=2017&termGbn=week|title=Because of You|website=[[Gaon Chart]]|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" |Soundtrack appearances\n|-\n! scope=row |\"Tomorrow Will Come\"\n|2014\n|\u2014\n|{{N/a}}\n|''Bonnie & Clyde The Musical'' OST\n|-\n! scope=row | \"You're My Love\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201507271737085089479_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Park Hyung-sik sings \u2018High Society\u2019 soundtrack|date=July 25, 2017|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> \n|2015\n| \u2014\n|{{N/a}}\n|''[[High Society (2015 TV series)|High Society]]'' OST\n|-\n! scope=row | \"I'll Be Here\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2017\n| \u2014\n| {{N/a}}\n|''[[Hwarang: The Poet Warrior Youth]]'' OST\n|-\n! scope=row | \"[[True Colors (Cyndi Lauper song)|True Colors]]\"<br>{{small|(with [[Lee Sung-kyung]])}}\n| \u2014\n|{{N/a}}\n|''[[Trolls (film)|Trolls]]'' OST (Korean version)\n|-\n! scope=row | \"Because of You\"\n|85\n| \n* KOR: 22,038+<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=S1020&targetTime=16&hitYear=2017&termGbn=week|title=2017 Gaon Download Chart \u2013 Week 16|website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=April 27, 2017}}</ref>\n|''[[Strong Girl Bong-soon]]'' OST\n|-\n! scope=row | \"Two Lights\"\n| \u2014\n|{{N/a}}\n|''Two Lights: Rel\u00fam\u012dno'' OST\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" |<small>\"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart or were not released in that region.</small>\n|}\n\n===As producer===\n{| class=\"wikitabl